<aura:documentation>
	<aura:description>
        A generic lightning component to handle aura exceptions gracefully by returning a toast message.<br/>
        Used the answer provided to the question at <a href="https://salesforce.stackexchange.com/questions/176979/best-practice-for-catching-and-displaying-action-errors-in-lightning-components/177007#answer-177007">StackExchange</a> to implement this component.<br/>
        Implemented a basic try catch logic on top of the code to handle any errors in the callback function.
        This allows for handling error messages when the component is used outside of the one.app context
    </aura:description>
</aura:documentation>